description:
Provides RKE cluster resource. This can be used to create RKE clusters and retrieve their information.

RKE clusters can be defined in the provider:
- Using cluster_yaml: The full RKE cluster is defined in an RKE cluster.yml file.
- Using the TF provider arguments to define the entire cluster.
- Using a combination of both the cluster_yaml and TF provider arguments. The TF arguments will override the cluster_yaml options if collisions occur.

tfcfnid.description: Internal identifier for tracking resource changes. Do not use.

AddonJobTimeout.description: RKE k8s cluster addon deployment timeout in seconds for status check (int).

Addons.description: RKE k8s cluster user addons YAML manifest to be deployed (string).

AddonsInclude.description: RKE k8s cluster user addons YAML manifest urls or paths to be deployed (list).

ClusterName.description: RKE k8s cluster name used in the kube config (string).

ClusterYaml.description: RKE k8s cluster config yaml encoded. Provider arguments take precedence over this one (string).

CustomCerts.description: Use custom certificates from a cert dir (string).

DelayOnCreation.description: RKE k8s cluster delay on creation (int).

Dind.description: Deploy RKE cluster on a dind environment. Default: `false` (bool).

DisablePortCheck.description: Enable/Disable RKE k8s cluster port checking. Default `false` (bool).

IgnoreDockerVersion.description: Enable/Disable RKE k8s cluster strict docker version checking. Default `false` (bool).

KubernetesVersion.description: K8s version to deploy. If kubernetes image is specified, image version takes precedence. Default: `rke default` (string).

UpdateOnly.description: Skip idempotent deployment of control and etcd plane. Default `false` (bool).
